FulQrun Implementation Roadmap
Phase 1: MVP
üëâ Goal: Validate core value proposition (PEAK + MEDDPICC embedded sales operations). Lightweight, fast iteration using Cursor + Claude Code for scaffolding, integration stubs, and rapid feature delivery.
Core Modules
‚Ä¢	Authentication: Supabase + Microsoft Entra ID SSO
‚Ä¢	Opportunity Management (basic PEAK stages + MEDDPICC qualification fields)
‚Ä¢	Lead Management (manual entry + basic scoring rules)
‚Ä¢	Contact & Company Management (light CRM)
‚Ä¢	Basic Analytics (pipeline by stage, deal conversion rate)
‚Ä¢	Microsoft Graph + Exchange integration (emails, calendar sync)
‚Ä¢	QuickBooks integration for invoicing (stubbed with test accounts)
‚Ä¢	Role-based dashboards (rep, manager, admin)
‚Ä¢	Mobile-responsive PWA frontend
Dev Setup in Cursor/Claude
‚Ä¢	Cursor: Generate Next.js boilerplate with Tailwind UI, TailwindCSS, and Supabase auth scaffolds.
‚Ä¢	Claude Code: Use for Supabase schema design (tables for leads, opportunities, contacts, users, orgs). Generate migrations + row-level security rules.
‚Ä¢	Automated CI/CD ‚Üí Vercel (frontend + edge functions) + Supabase.
‚Ä¢	Prompt Claude to auto-generate unit tests and integration mocks.
Deliverable: Functional MVP demo ‚Üí early adopter sales teams (5‚Äì10 users per branch).



 

Phase 2: v1.0
üëâ Goal: Achieve feature parity with mid-market CRMs + establish differentiators (methodology-driven workflows, early AI layer).
Feature Expansion
‚Ä¢	Advanced Pipeline Configurability (drag-and-drop builder + workflow automation).
‚Ä¢	Full PEAK Process Integration (Prospect ‚Üí Engage ‚Üí Acquire ‚Üí Keep workflows, SharePoint repos).
‚Ä¢	Expanded MEDDPICC Qualification (AI hints for metrics, champion detection).
‚Ä¢	Financial Management: POS + inventory module.
‚Ä¢	Performance Management: CSTPV dashboards + drill-down analytics.
‚Ä¢	AI-driven insights: predictive lead scoring, deal risk scoring, ‚Äúnext best action‚Äù prompts.
‚Ä¢	Open Integration Hub v1 (Slack, DocuSign, Gong/Chorus, Stripe).
‚Ä¢	FulQrun Learning Platform (certifications for reps, embedded micro-learning).
‚Ä¢	Enhanced Compliance: GDPR + HIPAA-ready logs, versioned regulatory docs.
Dev Setup in Cursor/Claude
‚Ä¢	Cursor: Pair-program complex UI features (pipeline builder, analytics dashboards).
‚Ä¢	Claude Code: Auto-generate Supabase edge functions for AI integrations (OpenAI/Anthropic for deal risk, summarization, insights).
‚Ä¢	Create API middleware layer for third-party integrations ‚Üí reuse connectors pattern.
‚Ä¢	Expand test coverage (Claude-driven unit + Playwright end-to-end tests).
Deliverable: v1.0 SaaS release ‚Üí scalable for mid-size enterprises (50‚Äì250 users).








 
Phase 3: Enterprise Scale 
üëâ Goal: Full enterprise-grade platform to compete with Salesforce/Dynamics.
Feature Expansion
